<Section xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation" xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml" Background="Salmon">
	<Table CellSpacing="5">
		<Table.Resources>
			<Style x:Key="CellStyle1" TargetType="{x:Type TableCell}">
			    <Setter Property="FontFamily" Value="Verdana" />
			    <Setter Property="FontWeight" Value="Bold" />
			    <Setter Property="Foreground" Value="red" />
			    <Setter Property="FontStyle" Value="Italic" />
				 <Setter Property="ColumnSpan" Value="2" />
			</Style>
			<Style TargetType="{x:Type TableCell}">
			    <Setter Property="FontFamily" Value="Comic Sans MS" />
			    <Setter Property="FontSize" Value="12pt" />
			    <Setter Property="BorderThickness" Value="1,1,1,1" />
			    <Setter Property="BorderBrush" Value="green" />
			</Style>
			    <Style x:Key="RowStyle1" TargetType="{x:Type TableRow}">
			    <Setter Property="Foreground" Value="White" />
			</Style>
			    <Style x:Key="RowGroupStyle1" TargetType="{x:Type TableRowGroup}">
			    <Setter Property="Background" Value="Tan" />
			</Style>
			     <Style x:Key="ColumnStyle1" TargetType="{x:Type TableColumn}">
			    <Setter Property="Width" Value="150" />
			</Style>
			     <Style TargetType="{x:Type FlowDocument}">
			    <Setter Property="Foreground" Value="blue" />
			    <Setter Property="FontFamily" Value="Times New Roman" />
			    <Setter Property="FontSize" Value="20px" />
			</Style>
		</Table.Resources>
		<Table.Columns>
			<TableColumn />
			<TableColumn Style="{DynamicResource ColumnStyle1}"/>
		</Table.Columns>    
		<TableRowGroup Style="{DynamicResource RowGroupStyle1}">
			<TableRow>
				<TableCell Padding="4,4,4,4" FontSize="10pt" Foreground="yellow"><Paragraph>Can Ganguly lift India from Down Under?</Paragraph></TableCell>
				<TableCell Padding="4,4,4,4" FontSize="10pt" Foreground="yellow"><Paragraph>Column 2</Paragraph></TableCell>
			</TableRow>
		</TableRowGroup>
		<TableRowGroup>
			<TableRow>
				<TableCell><Paragraph>NEW DELHI: India's skipper Sourav Ganguly could not have timed his return to the team any better. <FlowDocumentScrollViewer><FlowDocument><Paragraph>This is a big week for Indian cricket with big matches against Australia and New Zealand.</Paragraph></FlowDocument></FlowDocumentScrollViewer>There is of course the added chance of India crashing out of the series if they botch up both of their matches. </Paragraph></TableCell>
				<TableCell Padding="4" Foreground="yellow"><Paragraph>Column 2</Paragraph></TableCell>
			</TableRow>
			<TableRow>
				<TableCell Style="{DynamicResource CellStyle1}"><Paragraph>Australia top the points table with 23 points, comprising four wins in a row. The Kiwis have 10 points from five matches while India are on nine from four matches. <LineBreak /> With Australia already assured of a berth in the finals, the Bangalore match is only of academic value. India has to win against New Zealand at Hyderabad on Saturday to book a place in the final to be played at Kolkata on November 18.</Paragraph></TableCell>
			</TableRow>
			<TableRow Style="{DynamicResource RowStyle1}">
				<TableCell><Paragraph>The HR Intranet provides general information and guidelines only. It does not create any contractual rights or guarantee specific treatment in any given situation.</Paragraph></TableCell>
				<TableCell Padding="4,4,4,4" FontSize="10pt" Foreground="yellow"><Paragraph>Column 2</Paragraph></TableCell>
			</TableRow>	
		</TableRowGroup>
	</Table>
</Section>